			Git Stash
		==================
		This feature is used for leaving unfinished work, in such a way that Git cannot access it and continue to work on some other files.

		Further commands of git should be able to process only  the new files.
		This can be done using git stash.
		
	 git stash / git stash save " updated some code"
	 git stash list
	 git stash show --> This command shows the summaary of the stash diffs.
	 git stash show -p --> It will give you the detailed list of differences.
	 
	 stash@{0}
	 stash@{1}
	 
	 git stash apply --> It will apply latest of stash
	 git stash apply  stash@{1}--> It will apply the specified stash
	 git stash drop --> It will drop from your stack.
	 
	
	# We have to save/store the stash in temp
	git stash 
	git stash list
 	
	#we can use only one command insted of stash apply and drop for restore the stashed
	 git stash pop --> It apply the latest stash and then immediatly drop it from your stack.
	 git stash pop stash@{1} --> It will apply the purticular stash and then immediatly drop it from your stack.
			
			Commands
				--------------------
		1) To stash  the stagged files
		 $  git  stash

		2) To stash  staged and untracked files
		$  git  stash  -u

		3) To see the list of stashes
			git  stash  list

		4) TO get back the stashed files
		   git  stash pop

		5) to bring the older stash  out
		  git  stash  pop  stash@{stash_number}
		  
		
