		Git  rebase
	====================
	git merge :- we have to integrate from branch to another branch
	git rebae :- rebase also integrate from branch to another branch
	
	# Then what is the diff b/w git merge and rebase???
	1. git merge and rebase both are going to integrate from branch to another branch.
	
	master -- MC1 -- MC2 -- MC3
						|
						|
						V
				Development -DC1 - Dc2 - Dc3 -DC4 -DC5 
				
	git merge development --> It will integrate all commits to master in single object(we donn't know how many commits in dev branch and also there is no clear picture in master aslo how many commits integrated)
	git rebase development--> It will integrate all commits to master as it is as from Dev (after commited in master It will be clear picture all commits)
	
	This is called as fastforward merge.
	The commits from the child branch are added to the top of the master branch.
	This is helpful when we want code from a branch to be reflected as the latest working version on master.
	
